Risks Related to Economic Conditions, Financial Markets and Operating Internationally

• The risks associated with global operations on the Company and its customers and suppliers,

 including foreign governments in countries in which the Company operates;

• The impact of inflation and fluctuations in interest rates and currency exchange rates and the potential effect of such fluctuations on revenues,

 expenses and resulting margins;

• Potential changes in export/import and trade laws,

 regulations and policies of the United States and other countries, including any increased trade restrictions or tariffs and potential drug reimportation legislation;

• The impact on international operations from financial instability in international economies, sovereign risk,

 possible imposition of governmental controls and restrictive economic policies,

and unstable international governments and legal systems;

• The impact of global public health crises and pandemics,

 including the novel coronavirus (COVID-19) pandemic;

